    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Drop CustomerID for analysis\n",
        "features = df.drop(columns=['CustomerID'])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GKbYeZmyuSkg"
      },
      "execution_count": 41,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Convert categorical 'Gender' to numeric\n",
        "features = pd.get_dummies(features, drop_first=True)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "U2sYyrBVuSnS"
      },
      "execution_count": 42,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ccBXl2F_uXyu"
      },
      "execution_count": 43,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Standardize the features\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "scaled_features = scaler.fit_transform(features)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "rEIAoNLMufEi"
      },
      "execution_count": 44,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**1.Load and visualize dataset (optional PCA for 2D view).**\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "DNXsodkyvGZY"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Djc6fSeEuhQg"
      },
      "execution_count": 45,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Apply PCA to reduce to 2 components for visualization\n",
        "pca = PCA(n_components=2)\n",
        "pca_result = pca.fit_transform(scaled_features)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3QqzGwuruhWr"
      },
      "execution_count": 46,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Create a DataFrame for PCA results\n",
        "pca_df = pd.DataFrame(data=pca_result, columns=['PC1', 'PC2'])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4WyfUeBiume5"
      },
      "execution_count": 47,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Plot the PCA results\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))\n",
        "sns.scatterplot(x='PC1', y='PC2', data=pca_df, hue=df['Gender'], palette='pastel')\n",
        "plt.title('PCA Visualization of Mall Customers')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Principal Component 1')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Principal Component 2')\n",
        "plt.legend(title='Gender')\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "metadata": {

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**2.Fit K-Means and assign cluster labels**"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "fB04t855vQeP"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "BRhzAyRpvDwY"
      },
      "execution_count": 49,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Apply KMeans with an initial assumption of 5 clusters\n",
        "kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=5, random_state=42)\n",
        "cluster_labels = kmeans.fit_predict(scaled_features)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "eRaIX65evD2L"
      },
      "execution_count": 50,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Add cluster labels to the PCA dataframe\n",
        "pca_df['Cluster'] = cluster_labels"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_RK68yJQvWn7"
      },
      "execution_count": 51,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Visualize the clusters in PCA-reduced space\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
        "sns.scatterplot(x='PC1', y='PC2', data=pca_df, hue='Cluster', palette='Set2', s=70)\n",
        "plt.title('K-Means Clustering Results (Visualized via PCA)')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Principal Component 1')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Principal Component 2')\n",
        "plt.legend(title='Cluster')\n",
        "plt.grid(True)\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**3.Use the Elbow Method to find optimal K**"
      ],
